definitions.definition: The process of gathering the ripened crop ; harvesting .
examples: The constant rain made the harvest a nightmare this year.

definitions.definition: The yield of harvesting, i.e., the gathered crops or fruits.
examples: This year's cotton harvest was great but the corn harvest was disastrous.

definitions.definition: The product or result of any exertion or course of action; reward or consequences.
examples: The surveillance mission yielded a healthy harvest of intel.

definitions.definition: The season of gathering ripened crops; specifically, the time of reaping and gathering grain .
The third season of the year; autumn ; fall .
examples: Harvest is usually very damp and rainy.

definitions.definition: A modern pagan ceremony held on or around the autumn equinox , which is in the harvesting season.

main_definition: ( agriculture ) The process of gathering the ripened crop ; harvesting .
secondary_definitions: The yield of harvesting, i.e., the gathered crops or fruits.
( by extension ) The product or result of any exertion or course of action; reward or consequences.
The season of gathering ripened crops; specifically, the time of reaping and gathering grain .
( UK , dialectal ) The third season of the year; autumn ; fall .
( paganism ) A modern pagan ceremony held on or around the autumn equinox , which is in the harvesting season.
